I ordered some Nintendo Switch Joy-Cons, the price seemed appropriate and the listing looked normal. Seller feedback is 96.2. No biggie. Until I realized that the account was opened March 2019, and first review was on January 10th 2020. The listing has the "money back guaranteed" thing on it, so do I have anything to worry about? Besides having to file a claim if it doesn't come, etc. 

Also noted that clicking through the feedback, it's a weird array of items. Blenders, hand truck dolly, a handful of feedback for the same baby angel costume ($4.60, which seems like it could be fake feedback, right?). Please help ease my mind!
